-fill Exercise Post-Listening Exercise How do your own movie preferences compare with the woman&#8217;s likes and dislikes in the conversation? Think of words or phrases to describe these genres types of movies: action, anime, classics, comedy, drama, documentary, foreign, horror, musicals, romance, science fiction, thrillers Example : documentary &#8211; interesting and informative Online Investigation Research two online movie rental services and compare them in terms of price, service, movie selection, and delivery. Discuss your findings. Keep Learning With Related Language Activities 🎧 Related Listening Activity ▶️ Related Video Lesson ✅ Next Level Challenge 📝 Self-Study Guide ⭐ Randall&#8217;s Favorites .lesson-links { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 0px 0 0px 0; } .lesson-link { color: #174973; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.2s; } .lesson-link:hover { color: #005a87; text-decoration: underline; } ◄ Previous Activity Next Activity ► See Listening Script Back to Easy Quizzes Language Games Try More Free Listening at DailyESL.com Follow Randall: (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); Study Guide Academic English Listening Basic English Quizzes Easy Listening Intermediate Listening Difficult Listening English Grammar Lessons Interviews English Idioms English Culture Videos ESL Vocabulary Quizzes medianet_width = "300"; medianet_height = "600"; medianet_crid = "621252724"; medianet_versionId = "3111299"; (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});',N'text',@Now,0); GO
